	<section>
		    <section>
			<h2>Document Object Model</h2>
			<ul>
			    <li>Defines standard way for accessing and manipulating HTML documents</li>
			    <li>Represents html document as a tree structure</li>

			</ul>
		    </section>
		    <section>
			<h2>Document Object Model</h2>
			<pre><code contenteditable>
<!DOCTYPE HTML>
&lt;html lang="en-GB">
&lt;head&gt;
    &lt;title&gt;Ka-pow!&lt;/title&gt;
&lt;/head&gt;
&lt;body&gt;
	&lt;div id="lonely"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;div id="single_dad"&gt;
		&lt;div class="daddys_boy"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;div class="daddys_girl"&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/body&gt;
&lt;/html&gt;
</code>
			</pre>
			<p><img src="../img/dom.png" alt="DOM" /></p>
		    </section>
		    <section>
			<h2>Try it!</h2>
			<ol>
			    <li>Use Chrome Dev Tools - Elements Tab to View and Edit DOM (F12 in Chrome)</li>
			    <li>Note: there can only be one element with a given id, but many with the same class.</li>
			</ol>
		    </section>
		</section>